caller_intent: Yolanda is addressing a $55 liability charge from the Department of Transportation (DOT) related to a vehicle insured by Alliance Insurance, seeking clarification and resolution.
resolution_steps: Agent advises Yolanda not to pay the $55 charge immediately.
Requests Yolanda to resend the DOT email/form via email to 'support@myallianceinsurance.com' (specifically the support team, not the agent's personal email).
Explains that the support team (Brandy, JC, and others) will handle the claim and that delays may be due to DMV processing issues.
Schedules a follow-up in one week to check on the status.
knowledge_required: Understanding of DMV claim processes and liability charges
Knowledge of internal support team structure and communication protocols
Ability to differentiate between legitimate claims and potential errors in billing
summary: Yolanda discusses a $55 liability charge from the DOT related to an insured vehicle. The agent reassures her not to pay immediately, directs her to send documentation to the support team, and schedules a follow-up in one week. The agent attributes potential delays to DMV processing issues and confirms the support team will handle the claim.
